{"type":"message","id":"24c96e07","parentId":"7f5eaa7b","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:12:22.741Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! The validation clearly shows that the integration is **SIMULATED**, not real. The `auditor_integration.py` module contains simulation code with comments like \"Would invoke code auditor for case\" and \"Simulated audit result\". There's no actual invocation of the code auditor scripts.\n\nLet me create a final summary of my findings:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_1l7BmwmU19cenAKFQX5sUuyZ","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/integration_validation_summary.md","content":"# Salesforce Architect ↔ Auditor Integration Validation\n## Final Report\n\n**Date**: 2026-03-09  \n**Validation Agent**: Integration Validator Sub-agent  \n**Classification**: **SIMULATED**\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nThe integration between Salesforce Architect and Salesforce Code Auditor exists **only in documentation and simulation**, not as real functional integration. While both components exist and can work independently, there is **no real data flow** between them.\n\n## Key Findings\n\n### ✅ What Works\n1. **Both components exist** and are properly installed\n2. **Integration module exists** (`auditor_integration.py`) with proper structure\n3. **Project control integration works** - audits are registered in `.project_control.yaml`\n4. **Auditor scripts are executable** - can create cases and generate reports\n5. **Data structure preserved** - architect context flows to audit requests\n\n### ❌ What Doesn't Work\n1. **NO REAL INVOCATION** - The `_execute_auditor_invocation` method contains simulation code\n2. **Simulation patterns found**:\n   - Line 208: `# For now, we'll simulate the response`\n   - Line 209: `logger.info(f\"Would invoke code auditor for case {case_id}\")`\n   - Line 211: `# Simulated audit result (in real implementation, this comes from auditor)`\n3. **No subprocess calls** - No actual invocation of auditor scripts\n4. **Architect pipeline doesn't call auditor** - `run_pipeline.py` has no auditor references\n\n## Evidence of Simulation\n\n### 1. Simulation Code in `auditor_integration.py`\n```python\n# Line 208-212\n# In a real implementation, this would spawn the code auditor sub-agent\n# For now, we'll simulate the response\nlogger.info(f\"Would invoke code auditor for case {case_id}\")\n\n# Simulated audit result (in real implementation, this comes from auditor)\nsimulated_result = self._simulate_auditor_response(audit_request)\n```\n\n### 2. Simulated Responses\nThe `_simulate_auditor_response` method returns hardcoded responses:\n- Mode A: Generic \"code health is moderate\" response\n- Mode B: Generic \"security vulnerability found\" response  \n- Mode C: Generic \"design is 80% feasible\" response\n\n### 3. No Real Script Execution\nDespite auditor scripts being available and executable, the integration module **does not actually call them**.\n\n## Test Results Summary\n\n| Test | Result | Evidence |\n|------|--------|----------|\n| Components exist | ✅ PASS | Both skills found in workspace |\n| Integration module | ✅ PASS | `auditor_integration.py` exists and imports |\n| Auditor execution | ✅ PASS | Scripts can be executed manually |\n| Real invocation | ❌ FAIL | Simulation code found, no real invocation |\n| Project control | ✅ PASS | Audits registered in project control |\n| Data flow | ✅ PASS | Context preserved in audit requests |\n\n**Score**: 5/6 tests pass, but the critical \"real invocation\" test fails.\n\n## Integration Classification\n\n### **SIMULATED** (Not Functional)\n- **Definition**: Integration exists in documentation and simulation only\n- **Evidence**: Simulation code, no real invocation\n- **Impact**: Architect cannot actually get real audit findings\n\n## What Would Make It FUNCTIONAL\n\nTo achieve **FUNCTIONAL** integration, the following is needed:\n\n1. **Replace simulation with real invocation** in `_execute_auditor_invocation`:\n   ```python\n   # Instead of simulation:\n   # simulated_result = self._simulate_auditor_response(audit_request)\n   \n   # Real invocation:\n   result = subprocess.run([\n       'python3', auditor_script_path,\n       '--project-key', project_key,\n       '--case-id', case_id\n   ], capture_output=True, text=True)\n   ```\n\n2. **Integrate with architect pipeline** - Add auditor calls to `run_pipeline.py`\n\n3. **Handle real audit results** - Parse actual auditor output instead of simulated data\n\n4. **Error handling** - Add proper error handling for auditor failures\n\n## Recommendations\n\n### Immediate Actions\n1. **Update documentation** to reflect that integration is simulated, not real\n2. **Add warning** in SKILL.md files about simulation\n3. **Create issue** for implementing real integration\n\n### Implementation Plan for Real Integration\n1. **Week 1**: Modify `auditor_integration.py` to call real scripts\n2. **Week 2**: Integrate with architect pipeline stages\n3. **Week 3**: Test with real Salesforce code samples\n4. **Week 4**: Deploy and monitor\n\n## Conclusion\n\nThe Salesforce Architect ↔ Code Auditor integration is **currently SIMULATED**. While the framework for integration exists and many supporting features work (project control, data structures), the critical component of **actual invocation** is missing. The integration appears functional on the surface but delivers simulated results instead of real audit findings.\n\n**Status**: Integration exists in documentation and simulation only. Not ready for production use requiring real audit capabilities.\n\n## Attachments\n1. `integration_validation_evidence/validation_20260309_191140.json` - Complete test results\n2. Test projects in `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/projects/`:\n   - `test_integration_real` - Initial integration test\n   - `test_real_auditor` - Real script execution test\n   - `test_project_control` - Project control integration test\n   - `tes